65
00:08:46,545 --> 00:08:48,308
Excuse me sir
- Yeah... yeah

66
00:08:50,682 --> 00:08:51,944
Meet Maj. Binod Sengupta

67
00:08:52,184 --> 00:08:53,708
Hello sir
- Hello Karan

68
00:08:54,186 --> 00:08:55,915
And this is...
- We've already met, sir

69
00:08:56,121 --> 00:08:56,587
Good

70
00:08:57,923 --> 00:08:59,652
Akbar, you're going
to post 21 tomorrow?

71
00:08:59,858 --> 00:09:00,324
Yes sir

72
00:09:00,692 --> 00:09:03,661
I want the Operation Log and
analysis by tomorrow evening

73
00:09:03,862 --> 00:09:04,328
Right sir

74
00:09:05,130 --> 00:09:07,690
Take Karan along with you

75
00:09:09,634 --> 00:09:14,503
It's time you saw what
you've been sent here to defend

76
00:09:15,207 --> 00:09:15,673
Yes sir

77
00:09:18,877 --> 00:09:19,400
Come on

78
00:09:23,548 --> 00:09:24,845
Take it
- Thank you sir

79
00:09:30,055 --> 00:09:30,851
You see that

80
00:09:32,891 --> 00:09:35,689
These trophies, medals, certificates

81
00:09:37,395 --> 00:09:40,023
They were won in different
battles, on different fronts

82
00:09:41,066 --> 00:09:46,026
by the brave officers and
men of this regiment

83
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:52,370
Sometimes at the cost of their lives

84
00:09:54,746 --> 00:10:00,548
This regiment has always
given the nation and its army

85
00:10:01,486 --> 00:10:03,784
news of success and victory

86
00:10:05,257 --> 00:10:12,220
from this moment on,
you are a part of it's legacy

87
00:10:14,099 --> 00:10:15,566
these trophies belong to you too

88
00:10:17,269 --> 00:10:20,067
It is your duty to preserve
their honor and dignity

89
00:10:21,439 --> 00:10:22,565
And to help you do that

90
00:10:24,609 --> 00:10:29,410
you have the blessings and
faith of a billion people

91
00:10:32,117 --> 00:10:35,086
A billion people...

92
00:10:36,454 --> 00:10:41,084
who trust us to stay awake
so they may sleep

93
00:10:44,296 --> 00:10:50,758
This trust is a great
honor and a great responsibility

94
00:10:53,305 --> 00:10:56,763
You understand
- Yes sir

95
00:10:58,476 --> 00:10:58,942
Good

96
00:11:01,313 --> 00:11:02,940
Cheers gentlemen
- Cheers sir

97
00:11:03,815 --> 00:11:05,112
Hey, buck up

98
00:11:05,317 --> 00:11:07,285
To the net! Get to the net!
Hey come on

99
00:11:07,485 --> 00:11:10,113
...get upto the net! Not under it!

100
00:11:11,823 --> 00:11:14,121
What's the score?
Is anyone winning?

101
00:11:14,326 --> 00:11:16,294
Good morning sir
- Hey, morning

102
00:11:16,828 --> 00:11:18,796
Shall I put your clothes in the room?

103
00:11:18,997 --> 00:11:21,625
Yes and... keep the keys with you

104
00:11:31,843 --> 00:11:33,970
Wife?
- No

105
00:11:34,512 --> 00:11:37,970
Girl friend?
- I don't know Shall we go, sir?

106
00:11:38,183 --> 00:11:39,150
Sure, let's go

107
00:11:47,859 --> 00:11:49,827
Good morning Sir!
- You go ahead

108
00:11:53,031 --> 00:11:54,157
Aren't you playing today?

109
00:11:54,366 --> 00:11:55,663
No, pritam Singh, Sahib

110
00:11:55,867 --> 00:11:59,325
Karan, this is Sgt. Maj. Pritam Singh,
he is Lt. Shergill

111
00:11:59,537 --> 00:12:00,834
Welcome, sir

112
00:12:02,207 --> 00:12:07,839
pritam Singh is a very good man
and a respected veteran

113
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:12,009
It's officers like you
that have taught me all I know

114
00:12:12,884 --> 00:12:14,351
We should get going now

115
00:12:14,552 --> 00:12:15,849
Hail India (jai Hind)
- Jai Hind

116
00:12:27,399 --> 00:12:30,197
This is the last Indian village
before the Line of Control

117
00:12:30,735 --> 00:12:31,531
Soopra village

118
00:12:34,239 --> 00:12:36,537
Hello
- Hello

119
00:12:40,412 --> 00:12:41,538
Where are you from?

120
00:12:41,913 --> 00:12:42,538
Delhi

121
00:12:43,581 --> 00:12:44,377
The Capital

122
00:12:45,583 --> 00:12:46,709
I'm from Maliyabad

123
00:12:48,086 --> 00:12:50,884
Ever heard of it?
- Yes, sir

124
00:12:51,589 --> 00:12:52,385
When was that?

125
00:12:53,725 --> 00:12:56,717
Just now sir, from you!

126
00:13:13,945 --> 00:13:16,743
This highway goes along
the river from Srinagar to Leh

127
00:13:18,283 --> 00:13:20,410
It's the only link
between Kashmir and Ladakh

128
00:13:23,455 --> 00:13:24,251
You see those mountains?

129
00:13:25,457 --> 00:13:28,915
The LOC is behind that range

130
00:13:29,961 --> 00:13:33,089
and across it are pakistani posts

131
00:13:33,965 --> 00:13:34,954
You'll see it today

132
00:13:52,484 --> 00:13:54,952
Everything okay here?
- Yes, sir. Nothing to worry

133
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,117
Where's Capt. Ravindran?
- In the bunker, sir

134
00:13:57,655 --> 00:13:58,952
Allright, carry on

135
00:14:03,661 --> 00:14:07,119
Do you see the pakistani
post over there?

136
00:14:16,341 --> 00:14:19,310
Wow! Unbelievable

137
00:14:21,679 --> 00:14:24,477
That pillar marks the LOC

138
00:14:25,683 --> 00:14:27,651
and from here to there
is no man's land...

139
00:14:28,686 --> 00:14:29,653
Not ours Not theirs

140
00:14:30,688 --> 00:14:31,985
Even so, we exchange
fire almost every day

141
00:14:33,191 --> 00:14:34,488
If there's firing
we also retaliate

142
00:14:36,861 --> 00:14:37,828
That's amazing

143
00:14:38,863 --> 00:14:40,490
It's like I've always known,
but somehow...

144
00:14:41,699 --> 00:14:44,497
I've never felt this Indian before

145
00:14:47,372 --> 00:14:48,168
I'm an Indian

146
00:14:49,541 --> 00:14:53,500
I still remember seeing
these borders for the first time

147
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:57,177
I understand how you must feel

148
00:14:58,883 --> 00:14:59,850
Come, let's go

149
00:15:16,734 --> 00:15:19,532
I have been moved by
the affection and hospitality...

150
00:15:20,405 --> 00:15:21,531
...extended to me...

151
00:15:22,907 --> 00:15:24,875
...and the delegation
of eminent persons...

152
00:15:25,910 --> 00:15:27,036
...who accompanied me

153
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:31,549
jammu and Kashmir is one
of the issues...

154
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:33,217
...we are discussing...

155
00:15:34,252 --> 00:15:36,720
...within the framework of
our composite dialogue

156
00:15:46,097 --> 00:15:49,066
You were watching our live
telecast from the Wagah border

157
00:15:49,601 --> 00:15:51,228
This is a historic day

158
00:15:51,436 --> 00:15:54,735
Today, India and pakistan
can hope that these steps...

159
00:15:55,106 --> 00:16:00,237
will bridge the distance
that has long divided us

160
00:16:00,945 --> 00:16:05,905
Stay tuned for the news
in English, Thank you

161
00:16:09,621 --> 00:16:13,113
Out. - Guruvindhar, was that okay?
- Perfect

162
00:16:16,628 --> 00:16:18,255
Romila, call for you

163
00:16:19,130 --> 00:16:19,755
Thank you

164
00:16:28,806 --> 00:16:31,434
Hi Rajiv, tell me?

165
00:16:32,977 --> 00:16:35,775
I've to read the news at 8,
lets meet after that

166
00:16:35,980 --> 00:16:37,447
Okay, bye

167
00:16:44,322 --> 00:16:45,118
Thanks

168
00:16:51,162 --> 00:16:56,464
This must be special
- What do you mean?

169
00:16:57,335 --> 00:16:59,462
I mean, we met by chance

170
00:17:00,171 --> 00:17:01,297
kept running into each other

171
00:17:02,006 --> 00:17:04,474
and now we're more than good friends

172
00:17:05,677 --> 00:17:09,636
There must be something special
- perhaps

173
00:17:12,850 --> 00:17:13,976
How about getting married?

174
00:17:14,686 --> 00:17:15,812
What do you think?

175
00:17:17,689 --> 00:17:19,486
Rajiv, its very sweet of you

176
00:17:20,024 --> 00:17:23,653
We're friends, why not
leave it at that?

177
00:17:24,696 --> 00:17:26,664
Do you plan on marrying
someone you hate?

178
00:17:30,201 --> 00:17:33,659
Look, it's not like you
don't know me or don't like me...

179
00:17:34,706 --> 00:17:38,005
I hope
- Of course I like you

180
00:17:38,209 --> 00:17:39,005
You know it

181
00:17:39,711 --> 00:17:40,678
Then what's the problem?

182
00:17:42,547 --> 00:17:44,344
I haven't thought about marriage

183
00:17:44,882 --> 00:17:45,678
So give it a thought now

184
00:17:50,221 --> 00:17:55,682
Okay, say you'll think of it
Or is it asking too much?

185
00:17:55,893 --> 00:17:57,690
No, it's not that

186
00:17:58,896 --> 00:17:59,692
I'll think about it

187
00:18:07,238 --> 00:18:08,034
Hi mom

188
00:18:08,239 --> 00:18:11,037
When did you come?
- A little while ago

189
00:18:12,243 --> 00:18:14,211
Dinner?
- I've eaten

190
00:18:17,415 --> 00:18:18,382
What're you reading?

191
00:18:19,083 --> 00:18:22,382
Have a lecture at 9 tomorrow,
just making some notes

192
00:18:30,261 --> 00:18:33,890
Rajiv asked me to marry him

193
00:18:38,269 --> 00:18:38,894
What did you say?

194
00:18:41,439 --> 00:18:42,235
What should I have said?

195
00:18:45,276 --> 00:18:50,908
I think... whatever it was
you and Karan shared

196
00:18:52,617 --> 00:18:53,584
...it's in the past?

197
00:18:55,286 --> 00:18:57,754
It's something like that

198
00:18:59,290 --> 00:19:00,416
What do you think?

199
00:19:02,293 --> 00:19:05,592
You can't spend the
rest of your life in mourning

200
00:19:08,633 --> 00:19:11,101
That's true but...

201
00:19:11,969 --> 00:19:12,765
But what?

202
00:19:14,972 --> 00:19:15,438
Nothing

203
00:19:25,983 --> 00:19:29,282
Come on! Come on

204
00:19:32,156 --> 00:19:32,952
Good shot

205
00:19:37,995 --> 00:19:39,121
Well done Karan! Well done

206
00:19:39,330 --> 00:19:40,456
Come on! Come on

207
00:19:46,671 --> 00:19:48,298
Hello sir
- Hi Karan

208
00:19:49,841 --> 00:19:50,637
You see that?

209
00:19:51,676 --> 00:19:52,301
Sir

210
00:19:52,677 --> 00:19:57,478
The snow is melting
Summer is here

211
